\displaystyle g(x)=\frac{4e^{x/4}}{(x^2+x)(1-x)}
(x^2+x)(1-x)
4e^{x/4}
p(x)=(x^2+x)(1-x)
f(x)=x^2+x
h(x)=1-x
\implies p'(x)=f(x)h'(x)+h(x)f'(x)\tag{product rule}
g(x)=\frac{4e^{x/4}}{(x^2+x)(1-x)}
 h(x)=\ln (g(x)) = \ln ( 4e^{x/4} ) -\ln (x^2 + x) - \ln (1-x) 
 h'(x) = \frac{1}{g(x)} \cdot g'(x) = \frac{e^{x/4}}{4e^{x/4}} -\frac{2x+1}{x^2+x}+\frac{1}{1-x} 
 g'(x)=g(x)\cdot h'(x) 
